1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,490
When an employee or someone in the employee's family was ill, John remembered.

2
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:07,250
He took time to compliment his staff individually for their off-the-job accomplishments.

3
00:00:08,080 --> 00:00:15,169
But the largest evidence of John's be-human philosophy showed up in the way he handled a dismissal problem.

4
00:00:15,520 --> 00:00:23,250
One of the employees who had been hired by John's predecessor simply lacked the aptitude and interest for the work involved.

5
00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:26,450
John handled the problem magnificently.

6
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:38,370
He did not use the conventional procedure of calling the employee into his office and giving him first the bad news and then second fifteen or thirty days to move out.

7
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:42,689
Instead, he did two unusual things.

8
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:53,010
First, he explained why it would be to the employee's personal advantage to find a new situation where his aptitudes and interests would be more useful.

9
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:59,490
He worked with the employee and put him in touch with a reputable vocational guidance consultant.

10
00:01:00,080 --> 00:01:04,370
Next, he did something else above and beyond the call of duty.

11
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:13,330
He helped the employee find a new job by setting up interviews with executives in other companies where the employee's skills were needed.

12
00:01:13,760 --> 00:01:21,890
In just 18 days after the dismissal conference, the employee was relocated in a very promising situation.

13
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:28,529
This dismissal procedure intrigued me, so I asked John to explain his thinking behind it.

14
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:30,370
He explained it this way.

15
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:35,169
There's an old maxim I've formed and held in my mind, he began.

16
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:39,489
Whoever is under a man's power is under his protection, too.

17
00:01:39,839 --> 00:01:45,249
We never should have hired this man in the first place, because he's not cut out for this kind of work.

18
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:49,729
But since we did, the least I could do was help him to relocate.

19
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:57,650
Anybody," John continued, can hire a man, but the test of leadership is how one handles the dismissal.

20
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:05,729
By helping that employee relocate before he left us, built up a feeling of job security in everyone in my department.

21
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:11,729
I let them know by example that no one gets dumped on the street as long as I'm here.

22
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:17,010
Make no mistake, John's Be Human brand of leadership paid off.

23
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:20,290
There were no secret gossip sessions about John.

24
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:23,249
He received unquestioned loyalty and support.

25
00:02:23,439 --> 00:02:30,240
He had maximum job security because he gave maximum job security to his subordinates.
